{"title": "Unsanitized user input in HTTP request (SSRF)", "summary": "  Applications should not connect to locations formed from user input. This rule checks for URLs containing user-supplied data. ", "description": "\n\nApplications should not connect to locations formed from user input.\nThis rule checks for URLs containing user-supplied data.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid using user input in HTTP URLs:\n\n```php\n$curl = curl_init(\"https://{$_GET['host']}');\n```\n\n\u2705 Use user input indirectly to form a URL:\n\n```php\nif ($_GET[\"host\"] == \"option1\") {\n  $host = \"api1.com\";\n} else {\n  $host = \"api2.com\";\n}\n\n$curl = curl_init(\"https://$host');\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-918"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/php_lang_http_url_using_user_input"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}